Installation guide
==================

## MongoDB ##
sudo apt-get install mongodb

## Nginx Web Server ##
sudo apt-get install nginx

## Ruby ##
curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable
source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm
rvm install 2.0.0
rvm use 2.0.0

cd rmixer
bundle install
cd ../api
bundle install


Deployment guide
================
In order to start de LiveMediaStreamer core it is only necessary to execute the compiled binary. 
This binary uses one argument: the TCP port to communicate with the Ruby middleware. It must be configured accordingly to this middleware, which is 7777 by default. 

$ livemediastreamer <port>

There are two ways for deploying the web GUI:

-- Rackup (Recommended only for testing purposes. Default port is 9292)

	$ cd livemediastreamerwebgui/api
	$ rackup –p<port>

-- Nginx + Unicorn (Recommended for non testing purposes. Default port is 80)

	It is necessary to configure nginx configuration file correctly. An example can be found in api/nginx.conf.example

	$ cd mixerwebgui/api
	$ mkdir tmp
	$ mkdir tmp/sockets
	$ mkdir tmp/pids
	$ mkdir log
	$ sudo service nginx restart
	$ unicorn –c unicorn.rb -D